Ferguson, Missouri police officers were shot at Tuesday night, as they tried to investigate a burglary call at one of the town's many buildings burned down in anti-cop riots. 

Officers were called to the shell of the old Beauty Town store on West Florissant Avenue on Tuesday night around 6pm, and found several suspects stealing hair products from the building's basement. 

While trying to arrest the suspects, the officers heard gunfire coming from the Park Ridge Apartments located behind the store. 

