They ducked for cover and then heard another round of fire coming from another location across the street. 

'It was a volley of rounds,' Ferguson police Sgt Harry Dilworth told St Louis Post-Dispatch.

They called for back-up and 15 to 20 minutes later, the area was cleared out and no one was injured. 

